% Write `pdd/commands/checkup_review_options.py`, the shared advisory-layer helpers for `pdd checkup` subcommands.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Role & Scope
This module exports a single Click option decorator (`review_option`) that attaches `--review off|explain` to any checkup subcommand, plus `reject_review_on_snapshot` to raise a usage error when `--review` is passed to `checkup snapshot`.

% Non-responsibilities
- Does not invoke LLM calls.
- Does not perform any deterministic checks.
- Does not define `--interactive`, `--apply`, or `--dry-run` in any usable form (write-layer, out of scope).

% Requirements
1. Export `review_option(func)`: a `click.option` decorator that adds `--review` with `type=click.Choice(["off", "explain"])`, `default="off"`, and a help string describing the advisory pass.
2. Export `reject_review_on_snapshot(review: str) -> None`: raises `click.UsageError` when `review != "off"`, with a message stating that `--review` is not supported on `checkup snapshot`.
3. Stub `--interactive`, `--apply`, and `--dry-run` as `hidden=True` options that raise `click.UsageError("not yet implemented")` when invoked; attach them via a separate exported decorator `_reserved_write_layer_options(func)` so they are never wired to production commands until the write-layer issue lands.
4. All exported names are importable from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/checkup_review_options.py`
